          The Challenge
        </h1>
        <p>
          Reach the summit of Mount Adams via the designated route in under 2h10.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Mount Adams Challenge is an entirely informal event to be undertaken by individuals seeking a personal challenge.
        </p>
        <p>
          <b>It is not a race.</b>
        </p>
        <p>
          The idea behind the challenge is to encourage fitness and enjoyment of the mountains, whether you're a North Country resident or friend from afar. Do it in a low-key, fun way on a schedule that works for you.
        </p>
        <p>
          The White Mountain Cafe and Bookstore and SAalt Pub accept no responsibility for your safety. You agree to this, when you undertake the Mount Adams Challenge.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="content-section">
        <h1 class="article-title">
          The Rules
        </h1>
        <p>
          The White Mountain Caf√© and SAalt Pub will congratulate you with the classic White Mountain Cafe latte drink of your choice, the beverage of your choice at SAalt Pub, a White Mountain Cafe sticker, and a very cool certificate courtesy of <a href="http://borealchickdesigns.com/" target="_blank">Borealchick Designs</a>.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="rules-content" class="module content">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="content-section">
        <ol>
          <li>
            Nothing is more important than your personal safety, and only you are responsible for your own safety. You are on your own in the mountains. Act with common sense. If you are uncertain of your ability, physical condition, or the weather, do not attempt the Mount Adams Challenge.
          </li>
          <li>
            Run with respect and good intention. Follow Leave No Trace's <a href="https://lnt.org/learn/7-principles" target="_blank">seven principles</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            Be honest with yourself and others. No cheating!
          </li>
          <li>
            Have fun and be supportive of others who are trying the challenge.
          </li>
          <li>
            If you are trying for a fastest-known time for the challenge, please share a GPS log with us.
          </li>
          <li>
            Be grateful that we have the White Mountain National Forest, and wild areas like this in which to play. Support the Forest in their work, and if you feel so inclined, support hard-working local trail clubs. The trails on which you'll be running are maintained by the <a href="http://www.fs.usda.gov/whitemountain" target="_blank">US Forest Service</a>, <a href="http://www.outdoors.org" target="_blank">Appalachia Mountain Club</a>, and <a href="http://www.randolphmountainclub.org" target="_blank">Randolph Mountain Club</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            Have fun!
          </li>
        </ol>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="route" class="module">
